#PROMPT PADRONIZADO - UTILIZADO NO NANOBANANA PRO - PARA O RESULTADO R4 e R5

## Identity-Preserved Full-Body Transfer 

## Prompt

```text
Analyze both input images carefully before generating the result.

imagem_0 = ORIGINAL (structural and scene base)

imagem_1 = MODELO (identity source)

TASK

Perform a full body subject identity transfer using imagem_1 as the identity source and imagem_0 as the structural base.

The objective is to replace the person in imagem_0 with the person from imagem_1 while preserving all structural, material and environmental elements from imagem_0.

STEP 1 — IMAGE ANALYSIS

First analyze imagem_1 (MODELO) and extract all transferable identity attributes including:

- facial identity and biometrics
- face shape and bone structure
- eyes, eyebrows, nose, lips and facial proportions
- skin tone, skin texture, pores and natural skin marks
- hair color, hair texture, density and hairstyle
- visible unique markers such as freckles, moles, scars, piercings or other defining features
- age appearance and facial characteristics
- visible exposed-skin characteristics

Then analyze imagem_0 (ORIGINAL) and identify all structural elements that must remain unchanged:

- body pose and orientation
- body proportions and posture
- head angle and camera perspective
- clothing design and garment structure
- fabric folds and textile behavior
- accessories, props and jewelry
- hand position, arm position and body placement
- background and environment
- framing and focal length
- lighting direction and shadow behavior
- color temperature and ambient light
- depth of field and focus characteristics
- overall scene composition

STEP 2 — ATTRIBUTE MAPPING

Transfer from imagem_1 (MODELO):

- complete recognizable identity
- facial geometry and identity defining features
- hair appearance and visible traits
- natural skin characteristics and facial micro details

Preserve from imagem_0 (ORIGINAL):

- body pose and body orientation
- clothing and garment details
- accessories and props
- hand placement and body structure
- background and full scene composition
- lighting, shadows and reflections
- camera perspective and framing

STEP 3 — REPLACEMENT RULES

Replace only the person’s biological identity in imagem_0 with the identity from imagem_1.

Do not modify:

- pose
- clothing
- accessories
- background
- lighting
- camera framing
- perspective
- scene composition

The person from imagem_1 must appear naturally integrated into the exact pose, clothing and environment of imagem_0.

STEP 4 — INTEGRATION REQUIREMENTS

Ensure:

- correct head pose adaptation
- consistent face to body scale
- natural neck and shoulder transition
- seamless blending between face, hair and body
- consistent skin tone adaptation between transferred face and visible body areas
- anatomically correct facial placement
- realistic hair behavior according to pose and lighting
- preserved interaction between clothing and body

STEP 5 — LIGHTING AND REALISM

Match the transferred identity with the lighting conditions of imagem_0:

- same light direction
- same shadow logic
- same color temperature
- same ambient lighting
- realistic highlights on skin and hair
- coherent contrast and exposure

Maintain:

- photorealistic skin texture
- visible pores and micro skin detail
- natural hair strands
- fabric microtexture
- natural facial imperfections
- high detail without oversmoothing

STEP 6 — ERROR PREVENTION

Avoid:

- identity drift
- face distortion
- stretched facial features
- misaligned eyes
- warped jawline
- unnatural neck transitions
- mismatched skin color
- double face artifacts
- hair smearing
- clothing deformation
- background changes
- pose deviation

FINAL GOAL

Generate a photorealistic full body identity replacement where the person from imagem_1 appears naturally in the exact pose, clothing, lighting and environment of imagem_0.

MODEL PRIORITIES

Identity fidelity: very high

Structure preservation: very high

Clothing preservation: strict

Background preservation: strict

Pose preservation: strict

Texture fidelity: maximum

Photorealism priority: maximum
```
